                <note rend="inline" type="source">867n.01/318</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">British Embassy</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-01-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 20, 1923</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Under date of October 2nd a communication was received by the American Embassy in
                    London from the British Foreign Office suggesting certain changes in previous
                    drafts of the proposed Convention relating to the Mandate for Palestine.</p>
                <p>While the Department is not adverse to proceeding with the consideration of this
                    question, it has been felt that in view of the Lausanne Conference it might be
                    agreeable to the British Foreign Office to await the termination of the present
                    negotiations with Turkey before continuing the correspondence for the conclusion
                    of the Palestine Mandate Convention.</p>
            </div>
